section.section:
When a commodity in bulk is transported by vehicle to a buyer and the weight, measurement, or count of the commodity serves as the basis for determination of the charge or cost of the commodity, the person who weighs, measures, or counts the commodity shall make, in ink or other indelible marking material, a delivery ticket or written statement that includes:
The date of issue;
The name and address of the seller;
The name and address of the buyer;
An accurate statement of quantity, expressed as follows:
For weight, the net weight in pounds or tons or in kilograms or metric tons of the international system of measurement and, if net weight is derived from gross and tare weight determinations, the gross and tare weight in the same system of measurement, as the net weight; and
For other measurement terms, the appropriate term in accordance with §§ 11-301 and 11-304 of this subtitle;
A complete identification of the commodity in bulk, expressed as follows:
For solid fuel, the kind and size; and
For any other commodity in bulk, the kind and size, if necessary for accurate identification and value determination;
The complete signature of the person who determines the quantity of the commodity in bulk and, if required, the weighmaster license number; and
The license number or other numbers and letters that identify the vehicle by which the commodity in bulk is transported.

When a commodity in bulk or goods is transported by vehicle as a service and the weight or measurement of the commodity serves as the basis for determination of the charge or cost of the service, the person who weighs or measures the commodity in bulk or goods shall make, in ink or other indelible marking material, a written statement that includes:
The date of issue;
The name and address of the seller;
The name and address of the buyer;
The name and address of the transporter of the commodity in bulk or goods, if the transporter is paid on the basis of the weight or measurement statement and is neither the seller nor the buyer;
An accurate statement of quantity, expressed as provided in subsection (a)(1)(iv) of this section;
A description of the commodity in bulk or goods, sufficient for its positive identification;
The complete signature of the person who determines the quantity of the commodity in bulk or goods, and, if required, the weighmaster license number; and
The license number or other numbers and letters that identify the vehicle by which the commodity in bulk or goods is transported.
